result.formatted_address: 79 Ho Pui St, Tsuen Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Miu Fat Chai

reviews.text: One of the most thorough vegetarian restaurants and filled to full request of how we preferred our dishes

Saturated in MSG. Typical Chinese vegetarian, shared table, service charge comes in the form of tea/water cost. Regardless of whether you consume any tra or water, you will be charged the 5-8 HKD fee. There are set lunch about 35 - 45 HKD meals. Nothing to speak of, wouldnt come again.

If you can read Chinese and don’t mind sitting on a table with other people (which is common in HK) this vegetarian is not too bad. It is a hole in the wall with lots of old people who eat there but for someone who has tried many different Canto vegetarian places I like their food. They are not cheap with the vegetarian meats and the price is cheap for good quality. Their chrysanthemum tea is nice and you can always go up to their little open kitchen/ counter (When you first walk in) to pick what you like to eat. 

Big Negatives are: the seating is cramped and the toilets are self flush from a water scooper from the sink which is not great. Decor is super simple and ceiling aircons are so dirty.
Wonderful food - Managed by the owner and family with love and care.
Food is ok but seating is a bit crowded, often that u have to share table with others.

result.name: 妙法齋

reviews.text: 好好味呀！持素身體好，功德無量

以前較多食晚飯 現較少去  
很意外此店有早茶  點心還可以  
我最不喜歡是外賣盒 到現有還是用發泡膠盒(質數較差) 每次外賣 發泡膠盒內都比熱的食物熱溶  希望他們可改微波爐盒  
為什麼仍光顧  因為在荃灣 傳統的齋菜比較少

素食店, 有飲早茶的地方。
可在此食到一籠籠蒸的素食點心(只限早上)
